01. Visualization with 'matplotlib'¶

  • originated from MATLAB's visualization
  • 2D line-plot, scatter-plot, bar-chart, histogram, pie-chart
  • ref. url : http://matplotlib.org/
In [1]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

Line Graph¶

show graphs INLINE or NOT¶

Spyder>IPython Console or Jupyter Notebook Code Cell

  • show graph on another pop-up window

    • %matplotlib qt

  • show graph among code cells

    • %matplotlib inline
In [2]:
%matplotlib inline
In [3]:
data1 = [10,14,19,20,25]
plt.plot(data1)
Out[3]:
[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x23a778cad68>]
  • if input of plt.plot() is just one array sequence, the value of array sequence is shown on the y-axis

draw another graph on another layout(=figure)¶

In [12]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

x = np.arange(-4.5, 5, 0.5)
y1 = 2*x**2
y2 = 5*x + 30
y3 = 4*x**2 + 10

plt.plot(x,y1)
plt.figure()
plt.plot(x,y2)
plt.show()
In [13]:
# close the figure
plt.close()

clear all graph on the figure

  • plt.clf()
  • plt.figure(N) : select(or indicate)d figure no.N
In [14]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# generate data
x = np.arange(-5,5,0.1)  
y1 = x**2 - 2
y2 = 20 * np.cos(x)**2

plt.figure(1)    #generate space no.1
plt.plot(x, y1)  #draw graph_01 on no.1 figure

plt.figure(2)    #generate space no.2
plt.plot(x,y2)   #draw graph_02 on no.2 figure

plt.figure(1)    #indicate space no.1
plt.plot(x,y2)   #draw one more graph(graph_02) on no.1 figure

plt.figure(2)    #indicate space no.2
plt.clf()        #clear all graphs on no.2 figure
plt.plot(x,y1)   #draw graph_01 on no.2 figure

plt.show()

subplots¶

In [15]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

x = np.arange(0,10,0.1)
y1 = 0.3*(x-5)**2 + 1
y2 = -1.5*x + 3
y3 = np.sin(x)**2 
y4 = 10*np.exp(-x) + 1 

plt.subplot(2,2,1)
plt.plot(x,y1)

plt.subplot(2,2,2)
plt.plot(x,y2)

plt.subplot(2,2,3)
plt.plot(x,y3)

plt.subplot(2,2,4)
plt.plot(x,y4)

plt.show()

set graph range¶

In [16]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

x = np.linspace(-5,5,7)   # generate 7 values in the range [-4,4]
y1 = x**3
y2 = 10*x**2 - 2

plt.plot(x, y1, x, y2)
plt.show()
In [17]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

x = np.linspace(-5,5,7)   # generate 7 values in the range [-4,4]
y1 = x**3
y2 = 10*x**2 - 2

plt.plot(x, y1, x, y2)
plt.xlim(-1,1)
plt.ylim(-3,3)
plt.show()
  • enlarge partialy(intersection part)
  • use xlim() and ylim() to enlarge particular region

  • location option
location of legend string code
optimized location best 0
upper right upper right 1
upper left upper left 2
lower left lower left 3
lower right lower right 4
right right 5
center left center left 6
center right center right 7
lower center lower center 8
upper center upper center 9
center center 10

In [38]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

city = ['Seoul', 'Incheon', 'Daejeon', 'Daegu', 'Ulsan', 'Busan', 'Gwangju']

lat = [37.56, 37.45, 36.35, 35.87, 35.53, 35.18, 35.16]
lon = [126.97, 126.70, 127.38, 128.60, 129.31, 129.07, 126.85]

pop_den = [16154, 2751, 2839, 2790, 1099, 4454, 2995]

size = np.array(pop_den)*0.2   #size of marker
colors = ['r','g','b','c','m','k','y']   #color of marker

plt.scatter(lon, lat, s=size, c=colors, alpha=0.5)
plt.xlabel('longitude')
plt.ylabel('latitude')
plt.title('population density 2017')

for x, y, name in zip(lon, lat, city):
    plt.text(x, y, name)

plt.show()

Bar Plot¶

In [39]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

member_IDs = ['mA_01', 'm_02', 'm_03', 'm_04']   # ID
before_ex = [27, 35, 40, 33]   # sit-up count before exercise
after_ex = [30, 38, 42, 37]   # sit-up count after exercise

n_data = len(member_IDs)    # 4 people -> 4 IDs
index = np.arange(n_data)   # generate array (0,1,2,3)
plt.bar(index, before_ex)   # bar(x,y)
plt.show()

In [45]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

member_IDs = ['mA_01', 'm_02', 'm_03', 'm_04']  
before_ex = [27, 35, 40, 33]   
after_ex = [30, 38, 42, 37]  

n_data = len(member_IDs)    
index = np.arange(n_data)   
barWidth = 0.4

plt.bar(index, before_ex, color='c', align='edge', width=barWidth, label='before')
plt.bar(index + barWidth, after_ex, color='m', align='edge', width=barWidth, label='after')

plt.xticks(index+barWidth, member_IDs)
plt.legend()
plt.xlabel('ID')
plt.ylabel('sit-up count')
plt.title('comparison before and after change')

plt.show()

In [53]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

fruit = ['apple','banana','strawberry','orange','grape']
result = [7, 6, 3, 2, 2]

explode_value = (0.1, 0, 0, 0, 0)

plt.figure(figsize=(5,5))
plt.pie(result, labels=fruit, autopct='%.1f%%', startangle=90, counterclock=False,
        explode=explode_value, shadow=True)                      # emphasize one slice & add shadow
plt.show()
